&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The data and content produced by the Market Size Analyst will enhance Mintel’s market size database and support the development&amp;nbsp;of the Market Dynamics product. These concise, self-contained outputs provide clients with market intelligence and clear data-&amp;nbsp;driven analysis, guiding further market exploration. The Analyst’s contributions elevate Mintel’s reputation as a trusted source for&amp;nbsp;high quality and trustworthy market intelligence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Be Doing:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secondary Research:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Conduct economic market research across 40 FMCG categories by identifying and utilising secondary sources available in the&amp;nbsp;local market to determine market sizes. Map the brand landscape, presenting findings in structured data formats for further analysis&amp;nbsp;in a global context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trade Interviews:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and maintain relationships with industry experts and conduct trade interviews, capture emerging trends and key insights, and ensure the accuracy and relevance of research deliverables.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Produce written content: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop category content by applying strong market knowledge and analytical skills to evaluate data outputs, generating&amp;nbsp;insights and reliable market forecasts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; collaboration: &lt;/strong&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to share industry expertise, support knowledge sharing, and enhance operational&amp;nbsp;efficiency across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Local Market Expertise:&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 3 years of residency in &lt;strong&gt;France&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;with a strong understanding of its business culture and consumer behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native fluency in both written and spoken &lt;strong&gt;(French)&lt;/strong&gt; is essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with FMCG markets and local retail structures is a strong advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data-Driven:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and critical thinking skills, with high attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with large sets of quantitative data from various sources to extract meaningful insights and narratives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Excel and written business English for data analysis and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open &amp;amp; Global Mindset:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal and communication skills, with confidence in conducting daily trade interviews via phone or Microsoft&amp;nbsp;Teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in outbound calling (e.g., for sales, research, or customer service) is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative approach with a willingness to share knowledge and work across teams in a global environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Senior Analyst - Advisory, China&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Advisory &amp;amp; Client Engagement&lt;br&gt;• Deliver insight-sharing sessions and advisory discussions based on research findings and written reports, clearly explaining complex analyses and implications.&lt;br&gt;• Respond to client briefs by shaping research frameworks, analysis structures and report narratives, rather than purely extracting data.&lt;br&gt;• Use pre-published Mintel Reports and research outputs to support client discussions, tailoring angles and focus to specific business questions.&lt;br&gt;• Present research-led insights to clients in a clear, structured and confident manner, ensuring findings are well understood and actionable.&lt;br&gt;• Work closely with Client Success and Commercial teams to support content-led advisory engagements, ensuring research outputs are aligned with client needs.&lt;br&gt;• Proactively communicate with clients on the most relevant research findings, market insights and report outputs for their business priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. Content &amp;amp; Insights Delivery&lt;br&gt;• Publish in-depth research reports combining market research and consumer insights, demonstrating Mintel’s expertise across consumer markets.&lt;br&gt;• Deliver Mintel Reports on time and to a consistently high quality standard, covering a range of categories and subject areas.&lt;br&gt;• Independently lead the end-to-end report workflow, including:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;o research design and scoping&lt;br&gt;o questionnaire design and research framework development&lt;br&gt;o primary and secondary data collection&lt;br&gt;o data analysis, validation and interpretation&lt;br&gt;o insight synthesis, storyline development and report writing&lt;br&gt;• Gather and assess relevant primary and secondary data for each market, working closely with Research Directors to develop accurate market, company and segmentation insights.&lt;br&gt;• Translate complex data and research findings into clear, structured and insight-led written content, aligned with Mintel’s reporting standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. Industry Engagement&lt;br&gt;• Monitor consumer, market and innovation trends, identifying the most relevant issues to explore through consumer research.&lt;br&gt;• Build and maintain relationships with industry contacts and experts to deepen understanding of factors influencing consumer behavior, innovation and company strategy.&lt;br&gt;• Integrate market knowledge, research findings and external inputs into coherent insight narratives that strengthen report quality and relevance.&lt;/p&gt;

